President Donald Trump issued a proclamation on United Nations Day, celebrating the achievements of the organization in promoting peace, delivering aid, and addressing international challenges. He emphasized the importance of nations pursuing their own programs of national revitalization and protecting the interests of their citizens. President Trump highlighted the United States' leadership in addressing global issues such as Iran's destabilization efforts and the crisis in Venezuela. He also called for essential reforms within the United Nations, including more equitable distribution of financial burdens and reallocating funds from failed programs to successful ones. The proclamation also acknowledged the sacrifices of men and women serving in UN missions and honored those who have lost their lives in pursuit of world peace.